headline: Tractor Supply (TSCO): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q3 Earnings?
summary: Since June 2024, Tractor Supply has been in a holding pattern, posting a small return of 4% while floating around $284.50. The stock also fell short of the S&P 500’s 12.9% gain during that period.
